---

<SectionPageLayout
  title="Sakai Community | Sakai LMS"
  description="Educators who work directly with teaching and learning drive Sakai's open-source development and innovation."
  kicker="The Sakai Community"
  heading="Community-Led Innovation"
>
  <article class="hard-border block-shadow-soft bg-[var(--sakai-paper)] p-6">
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-ink)]">
      Educators who work directly with teaching and learning drive Sakai's open-source development and innovation.
      Member institutions collaborate to enhance Sakai, create integrations, and develop new functionality for digital learning environments.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="hard-border block-shadow-soft bg-[var(--sakai-ink)] p-6 text-[var(--sakai-paper)]">
    <p class="sans text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--sakai-aqua)]">Latest PMC Update</p>
    <h2 class="sans mt-2 text-2xl font-black uppercase">Andrea Schmidt Elected To Sakai PMC</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-paper)]/90">
      Andrea Schmidt (Learning Experiences) is the newest elected member of the Sakai Project Management Committee (PMC).
      The PMC gets involved when broader project decisions are needed around Sakai direction or Apereo-backed resource use.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-paper)]/90">
      Andrea serves as Sakai QA Lead and brings more than two decades of technical quality experience. She has contributed to
      Sakai QA since 2017 and has led global QA coordination since August 2022, including weekly QA facilitation, regression
      planning, and Jira verification across releases.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-paper)]/90">
      PMC membership reflects sustained contribution and commitment to community goals. Most day-to-day Sakai decisions are still
      made in working groups closest to the work, with PMC engagement for significant cross-project matters.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-4">
    <article class="hard-border block-shadow-soft bg-white p-5">
      <h2 class="sans text-2xl font-black uppercase text-[var(--sakai-ink)]">Sakai Community Leadership</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-ink-soft)]">
        The Sakai community is coordinated by the Apereo Foundation and works together to create a cutting-edge learning environment.
        The Sakai Project Management Committee (PMC) provides strategic oversight through meritocratic selection and open, consensus-based decision making.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 grid gap-2 text-xs text-[var(--sakai-ink-soft)] md:grid-cols-2">
        {pmcMembers.map((member) => (
          <li class="hard-border bg-[var(--sakai-paper)] px-2 py-1">{member}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
      <a href="https://sakaiproject.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/CONF/overview?mode=global" class="sans mt-4 inline-block text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] underline">
        Explore Project Wiki
      </a>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="hard-border block-shadow-soft bg-[var(--sakai-ink)] p-6 text-[var(--sakai-paper)]">
    <h2 class="sans text-2xl font-black uppercase">Sakai Commercial Affiliates</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--sakai-paper)]/85">Commercial affiliates develop, host, and support Sakai.</p>
    <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-3">
      {affiliates.map((affiliate) => (
        <a href={affiliate.href} class="hard-border bg-[var(--sakai-paper)]/10 p-4">
          <h3 class="sans text-base font-black uppercase">{affiliate.name}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-paper)]/90">{affiliate.description}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hard-border block-shadow-soft bg-[var(--sakai-paper)] p-6">
    <h2 class="sans text-2xl font-black uppercase text-[var(--sakai-ink)]">Community Stories</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--sakai-ink-soft)]">
      The legacy Sakai site highlights practitioner stories from institutions using Sakai in real teaching environments.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-3">
      {communityStories.map((story) => (
        <article class="hard-border bg-white p-4">
          <h3 class="sans text-lg font-black uppercase text-[var(--sakai-ink)]">{story.name}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--sakai-ink-soft)]">{story.institution}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@SakaiCLE" class="sans mt-4 inline-block text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] underline">
      Watch Community Videos
    </a>
  </section>
</SectionPageLayout>
